And when was the last time
that she had something

01:53.429 --> 01:54.561
to eat or drink?

01:54.563 --> 01:56.296
About an hour ago, she had...

01:56.298 --> 01:58.665
she was drinking some tea.
She had a couple cookies.

01:58.667 --> 02:00.534
<i>Has she had any
fainting spells recently?</i>

02:00.536 --> 02:01.571
No. Never.

02:03.304 --> 02:04.704
How you doing, Agnes?

02:04.706 --> 02:06.305
You getting better?

02:06.307 --> 02:07.641
<i>Hey, I still need
to try that famous</i>

02:07.643 --> 02:09.008
<i>Bolognese of yours.</i>

02:09.011 --> 02:10.644
How'd you know
about Mom's Bolognese?

02:10.645 --> 02:12.679
<i>Who doesn't?</i>

02:12.681 --> 02:14.514
Good.

02:14.516 --> 02:15.581
Much better. Yeah.

02:15.583 --> 02:17.317
Your blood pressure's up.

02:17.319 --> 02:19.686
I think you just
needed some fluids.

02:19.688 --> 02:21.555
- <i>Do you feel better?</i>
- <i>Is she gonna be okay?</i>

02:21.557 --> 02:22.889
<i>Yeah, her color is coming back</i>

02:22.891 --> 02:24.691
<i>and her heart rate is down.</i>

02:24.693 --> 02:26.892
You just got kind of
wiped out there, huh?

02:26.894 --> 02:28.427
<i>Mm-hm.</i>

02:28.429 --> 02:32.299
Wait a minute.
Are you, um... Susette?

02:32.301 --> 02:33.533
- It's Paulette.
- I knew it was you.

02:33.535 --> 02:34.901
Oh, my God.

02:34.903 --> 02:36.703
Mama, it's Susette.

02:36.705 --> 02:38.739
- <i>Remember her from school?</i>
- <i>I remember you</i>

02:38.741 --> 02:40.706
<i>because you were one of the...</i>

02:40.708 --> 02:42.376
I guess the only parent

02:42.378 --> 02:44.414
who would let me call you
by your first name.

02:45.713 --> 02:48.548
I thought you were so cool.

03:06.668 --> 03:07.437
<i>Paulette!</i>

03:09.637 --> 03:11.437
Look at you!
It's so good to see you

03:11.439 --> 03:12.872
- back in the old neighborhood.
- I know.

03:12.874 --> 03:14.640
- Hi.
- I was just leaving you

03:14.642 --> 03:15.808
- a note with my number.
- Oh, great.

03:15.810 --> 03:17.076
I'm just running
to the hospital

03:17.078 --> 03:18.578
because Mom wants
some of her stuff.

03:18.580 --> 03:20.747
All right. Here you go, and...

03:20.749 --> 03:21.882
it was so great to see you.

03:21.884 --> 03:23.317
- I am calling.
- Great.

03:23.319 --> 03:24.685
- Bye.
- <i>Bye.</i>

03:34.529 --> 03:36.562
<i>Good morning, New London.</i>

03:36.564 --> 03:38.731
<i>Sports and weather
at the bottom of the hour,</i>

03:38.733 --> 03:41.701
<i>and now our top story.</i>

03:41.703 --> 03:43.003
<i>A new jobs report tells us</i>

03:43.005 --> 03:45.404
<i>what you already knew.</i>

03:45.406 --> 03:47.873
<i>The regional economy
isn't getting any better.</i>

03:47.875 --> 03:49.408
<i>This according to economists</i>

03:49.410 --> 03:51.378
<i>from the University
of Connecticut.</i>

03:51.380 --> 03:53.347
<i>Now, they're saying
jobs are scarce,</i>

03:53.349 --> 03:54.781
<i>and that there's no indication</i>

03:54.783 --> 03:56.849
<i>that's going to change
any time soon.</i>

03:56.851 --> 03:59.853
<i>Of course, unemployment has
been a big concern for years,</i>

03:59.855 --> 04:00.920
<i>many finding it difficult</i>

04:00.922 --> 04:02.955
<i>to secure even part-time work.</i>

04:02.957 --> 04:06.626
<i>So, what should we do
about the lousy economy?</i>

04:06.628 --> 04:08.662
<i>Our lines are wide open
right now,</i>

04:08.664 --> 04:11.365
<i>so call us and tell us
what you think...</i>

04:25.814 --> 04:27.781
Holy shit.

05:55.636 --> 05:57.607
Oh, my God.

06:07.583 --> 06:08.551
Shit.

06:55.963 --> 06:59.865
Well, I'd heard somebody
finally bought this place.

06:59.867 --> 07:01.000
I had to meet the person

07:01.002 --> 07:04.170
ballsy enough to paint it pink.

07:04.172 --> 07:06.305
Well, it's not pink.
It's "Odessa Rose".

07:06.307 --> 07:07.940
If you say so.-

07:07.942 --> 07:09.643
Hi. I'm Billy.

07:09.645 --> 07:12.978
- Billy Von Winkle.
- Oh, sorry. Susette Kelo.

07:12.980 --> 07:14.915
Nice to meet you,
Susette Kelo.

07:14.917 --> 07:15.915
<i>Welcome to the neighborhood.</i>

07:15.917 --> 07:17.149
Thank you.

07:17.151 --> 07:18.884
So, how do you like it?

07:18.886 --> 07:19.985
Well, the view sucks.

07:19.987 --> 07:22.021
Other than that, it's nice.

07:22.023 --> 07:23.990
- It's fantastic.
- Yeah.

07:23.992 --> 07:26.893
- Do you live nearby?
- I own the deli on the corner,

07:26.895 --> 07:28.627
and a couple other buildings
that I rent out.

07:28.629 --> 07:29.963
Cool. I've been
meaning to come by.

07:29.965 --> 07:31.764
It's great to have a deli.

07:31.766 --> 07:34.266
- How about now?
- I can't. Thank you, but...

07:34.268 --> 07:36.670
Come on. I'll let you
buy me a cup of coffee.

07:36.672 --> 07:38.905
I just have a lot
of work to do, so...

07:38.907 --> 07:41.110
Come on, Red.
We need the business.

07:43.812 --> 07:45.845
All right. You know,
let me just wash up

07:45.847 --> 07:46.980
and I'll meet you over there.

07:46.982 --> 07:48.081
Welcome to the neighborhood.

07:48.083 --> 07:49.819
- <i>I'll see you there.</i>
- Okay.

07:52.020 --> 07:54.653
- <i>So what's your story?</i>
- What?

07:54.655 --> 07:57.923
- You married? What?
- Oh. Twice.

07:57.925 --> 08:00.225
Yeah. One ex-husband
and one soon to be.

08:00.227 --> 08:02.163
Yeah? Which one
pays the mortgage?

08:04.865 --> 08:06.968
- This one.
- Good for you.

08:07.869 --> 08:10.937
So, what do you do? Huh?

08:10.939 --> 08:13.038
How do you make a living?

08:14.643 --> 08:15.809
I'm a paramedic.

08:15.811 --> 08:17.910
- No kidding, huh?
- Nope.

08:17.912 --> 08:19.278
Well, you'll do good business
in this town.

08:19.280 --> 08:21.247
Half the neighborhood's
on its last legs.

08:21.249 --> 08:22.949
Oh, yeah, I noticed.

08:22.951 --> 08:24.119
Wow.

08:26.054 --> 08:26.752
Man, does it always...

08:26.754 --> 08:29.254
is it like this all the time?

08:29.256 --> 08:31.824
Because it stinks.

08:31.826 --> 08:33.659
You'd think the pastrami
would kind of cover

08:33.660 --> 08:35.894
- the smell of the sewage plant.
- Well, not quite.

08:35.895 --> 08:37.630
I mean, we've been
complaining as far back

08:37.631 --> 08:39.164
as anybody can remember.
What are you gonna do?

08:39.166 --> 08:40.966
It's like talking
to a rock, right?

08:40.967 --> 08:42.302
Which is why I spearheaded

08:42.304 --> 08:44.269
Operation Caca de Pollo.

08:44.270 --> 08:47.006
What? Did you say "Caca"?

08:47.008 --> 08:48.341
I got a couple of big containers

08:48.343 --> 08:50.176
- <i>of chicken shit.</i>
- <i>No!</i>

08:50.178 --> 08:52.245
<i>I brought it to City
Hall, basically, dumped it,</i>

08:52.247 --> 08:54.813
<i>and everyone was gagging
and dry heaving.</i>

08:54.815 --> 08:56.982
<i>It took 'em weeks
to clean it up.</i>

08:56.984 --> 08:58.817
<i>Yeah. But, spent an
afternoon in jail for it</i>

08:58.819 --> 09:00.653
<i>but it was worth it.
It was worth it.</i>

09:00.655 --> 09:02.187
- <i>And I got on Leno.</i>
- <i>You did?</i>

09:02.189 --> 09:05.091
- <i>Jay Leno.</i>
- Was he... was he nice?

09:05.093 --> 09:06.158
- Very nice.
- Yeah.

09:06.160 --> 09:07.729
Very, very nice man.

09:17.238 --> 09:19.905
Your numbers are still strong.

09:19.907 --> 09:22.043
Hell, you've even got
some Democrats who like you.

09:24.112 --> 09:25.945
That is why
you're on my payroll.

09:25.947 --> 09:27.850
You do work miracles.

09:30.184 --> 09:32.121
But I do need one more.

09:34.055 --> 09:35.925
I want you to get me New London.

09:37.125 --> 09:39.893
What the hell's in New London?

09:39.895 --> 09:41.097
Absolutely nothing.

09:47.069 --> 09:49.369
I do like the concept.

09:49.371 --> 09:51.203
I just don't know
who could pull that off.

09:51.205 --> 09:53.038
We need somebody with clout,

09:53.040 --> 09:56.076
integrity, popularity,

09:56.078 --> 09:57.943
not tied to any party.

09:57.945 --> 10:00.980
- Riding in on a unicorn.
- I know someone.

10:00.982 --> 10:04.017
- <i>What's his name?</i>
- Her name...

10:04.019 --> 10:05.719
<i>is Charlotte Wells.</i>

10:07.122 --> 10:10.123
<i>She's president
of Walthrop College...</i>

10:10.125 --> 10:12.491
<i>with a Rolodex to kill for.</i>

10:12.493 --> 10:15.360
<i>PhD in French literature.</i>

10:15.362 --> 10:19.164
<i>Brains, relentless ambition.</i>

10:19.166 --> 10:20.999
<i>And a real charmer,</i>

10:21.001 --> 10:23.937
<i>if you know what I mean.</i>

10:23.939 --> 10:26.972
<i>Even her own husband
has never seen her unkempt,</i>

10:26.974 --> 10:27.976
<i>shall we say.</i>

10:30.344 --> 10:32.912
<i>Those of us who are blessed</i>

10:32.914 --> 10:34.047
with gifts must design

10:34.049 --> 10:36.783
a better world for the poor.

10:36.785 --> 10:39.451
- <i>But first...</i>
- <i>Mr. Governor.</i>

10:39.453 --> 10:41.221
<i>Charlotte Wells
here to see you.</i>

10:41.223 --> 10:43.291
Send her in.

10:46.962 --> 10:48.293
- Charlotte.
- <i>Peter.</i>

10:48.295 --> 10:49.796
Thanks for coming
on such short notice.

10:49.798 --> 10:51.934
Always lovely to see you.

10:54.169 --> 10:55.371
Mr. Governor.

10:57.838 --> 10:59.105
Strong handshake.

10:59.107 --> 11:00.773
Please.

11:00.775 --> 11:02.207
We take this
blighted plot of land

11:02.209 --> 11:03.942
by the sewage treatment plant

11:03.944 --> 11:05.043
and we redevelop it.

11:05.045 --> 11:07.113
We lure a world-class company

11:07.115 --> 11:08.782
to build some high-tech facility

11:08.784 --> 11:11.116
and boom.
Add jobs, tax revenue,

11:11.118 --> 11:12.818
economic miracle.

11:12.820 --> 11:14.120
It'll certainly
compliment the work

11:14.122 --> 11:15.254
you've already been doing.

11:15.256 --> 11:17.791
We rescue a struggling
blue-collar city,

11:17.793 --> 11:19.895
- <i>and everyone wins.</i>
- Well, Mr. Governor...

11:21.262 --> 11:23.296
I've been in the trenches,

11:23.298 --> 11:26.166
and it is a tall task

11:26.168 --> 11:27.966
trying to pull off
something like this

11:27.968 --> 11:29.101
in a town that takes

11:29.103 --> 11:31.370
five years to approve
a stop sign.

11:31.372 --> 11:32.971
All we need is the land.

11:32.973 --> 11:35.107
Land under jurisdiction
of a mayor

11:35.109 --> 11:37.009
who would give zero support.

11:37.011 --> 11:39.479
The State of Connecticut
will make sure that you succeed.

11:39.481 --> 11:41.380
N-L-D-C.

11:41.382 --> 11:43.216
New London
Development Corporation.

11:43.218 --> 11:45.150
It sounds familiar.

11:45.152 --> 11:46.985
NLDC was established in 1978

11:46.987 --> 11:49.254
with the goal of assisting
with economic development.

11:49.256 --> 11:50.389
Oh, that's right.

11:50.391 --> 11:52.225
<i>It's been gathering dust</i>

11:52.227 --> 11:53.326
ever since, so,

11:53.328 --> 11:55.195
we simply dust it off

11:55.197 --> 11:58.163
and give it to you.

11:58.165 --> 12:00.099
How generous.

12:00.101 --> 12:03.336
Now, why would you do that?

12:03.338 --> 12:04.937
<i>You lead the NLDC,</i>

12:04.939 --> 12:07.105
but the city officials
are familiar with it,

12:07.107 --> 12:09.274
so, they're comfortable.

12:09.276 --> 12:11.311
The NLDC finds a worthy project,

12:11.313 --> 12:12.445
and it gets funded

12:12.447 --> 12:14.214
thanks to the governor.

12:14.216 --> 12:16.148
I simply just can't be the face

12:16.150 --> 12:17.517
of the operation, obviously.

12:17.519 --> 12:19.255
Just the mastermind.

12:21.021 --> 12:23.121
I'll tell you what.

12:23.123 --> 12:25.258
Why don't you sleep on it?

12:25.260 --> 12:26.124
I have a fundraiser.

12:30.165 --> 12:31.129
It has been such a pleasure.

12:31.131 --> 12:32.197
Mm-hm.

12:32.199 --> 12:33.368
Hmm.

12:50.184 --> 12:52.284
- Hello?
- <i>Hi, it's Tim LeBlanc here.</i>

12:52.286 --> 12:55.187
<i>Your number came up
on my caller ID.</i>

12:55.189 --> 12:56.522
Oh, I'm sorry.

12:56.524 --> 12:59.057
I must have misdialed.
Sorry about that.

12:59.059 --> 13:01.226
- <i>Okay, well, I thought...</i>
- Thank you.

13:01.228 --> 13:02.495
- <i>...maybe you were the
customer who came in...</i>

13:02.497 --> 13:04.364
Listen, I can't...

13:04.366 --> 13:06.265
I can't buy anything.

13:06.267 --> 13:09.201
I can't donate anything.

13:09.203 --> 13:11.270
I apologize, it was a mistake,

13:11.272 --> 13:14.072
and would you please
take me off your list?

13:14.074 --> 13:15.508
Okay? Thanks a lot.

13:15.510 --> 13:17.076
- Bye-bye.
- <i>Okay.</i>

13:17.078 --> 13:18.613
<i>I'm not actually
a telemarketer...</i>

13:28.223 --> 13:30.226
Oh, shoot.

13:44.072 --> 13:46.205
If you go down this aisle,
you'll see picture frames

13:46.207 --> 13:47.273
up on the... up on the left.

13:47.275 --> 13:48.408
Yeah.

13:51.979 --> 13:54.379
Hi. Tim LeBlanc,
telemarketer speaking.

13:54.381 --> 13:55.948
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

13:55.950 --> 13:57.083
<i>Anyway, are you open right now?</i>

13:57.085 --> 13:59.585
You know what? I'm gonna be here
right up to the point

13:59.587 --> 14:01.486
- where I leave.
- <i>Oh. Good. All right...</i>

14:01.488 --> 14:04.389
- Good. You gonna come by?
- <i>No, I'll come over.</i>

14:04.391 --> 14:06.058
Risk it.

14:06.060 --> 14:07.396
Oh, my God.

14:11.598 --> 14:13.201
Now I have to go.

14:14.669 --> 14:16.269
- I do... I like the red one.
- Yeah.

14:16.271 --> 14:19.138
- It's just...
- Well, everything is half off.

14:19.140 --> 14:20.706
Well, it's just
that one's a little

14:20.708 --> 14:23.408
- out of my price range, so...
- How's that?

14:23.410 --> 14:24.610
- Oh, that's nice.
- All right?

14:24.612 --> 14:26.346
- Yeah.
- That's in excellent shape.

14:26.348 --> 14:28.514
- Cushions are good.
- Oh, they're beautiful.

14:28.516 --> 14:30.383
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

14:30.385 --> 14:34.086
- And everything's a half off.
- Great.

14:34.088 --> 14:36.655
- Even this?
- No, that's a million dollars.

14:36.657 --> 14:38.291
Oh.

14:38.293 --> 14:40.393
Oh, I'm... I...

14:40.395 --> 14:42.095
- do you deliver?
- <i>Sure.</i>

14:42.097 --> 14:44.563
- And... oh, thank you.
- Yeah.

14:44.565 --> 14:46.432
How much would that cost?

14:46.434 --> 14:49.168
How about a meal?

14:49.170 --> 14:49.969
Oh. I got...

14:49.971 --> 14:51.671
it doesn't have
to be a big meal.

14:51.673 --> 14:53.438
<i>Do you take checks?</i>

14:57.277 --> 14:59.512
No. No. Move
Jason to the morning.

14:59.514 --> 15:01.346
<i>Mr. Governor,
I have Charlotte Wells...</i>

15:01.348 --> 15:04.152
- Just a sec.
- <i>...on line one for you.</i>

15:05.386 --> 15:07.552
Is this the call
I've been waiting for?

15:07.554 --> 15:09.455
Well, it very well might be,

15:09.457 --> 15:11.025
Mr. Governor.

15:13.660 --> 15:16.395
Just one question.

15:16.397 --> 15:17.663
Why the sudden interest

15:17.665 --> 15:19.968
in my little town?

15:21.368 --> 15:22.302
Well, I care deeply

15:22.304 --> 15:25.370
about revitalizing
distressed communities.

15:25.372 --> 15:28.273
Well, if you would allow me
to take a wild guess

15:28.275 --> 15:30.342
at another reason...

15:30.344 --> 15:32.412
And what's that, Charlotte?

15:32.414 --> 15:33.413
Republican governor

15:33.415 --> 15:35.748
of Democratic state

15:35.750 --> 15:39.217
rescues struggling
Democratic city?

15:39.219 --> 15:43.322
<i>You're the hero.
You woo plenty of voters.</i>

15:43.324 --> 15:44.423
Maybe even myself

15:44.425 --> 15:46.458
and you win reelection

15:46.460 --> 15:47.559
in a landslide

15:47.561 --> 15:49.461
and more importantly,

15:49.463 --> 15:51.364
that kind of narrative
plays well

15:51.366 --> 15:53.131
on a national stage.

15:53.133 --> 15:55.370
- <i>Am I right?</i>
- Are you in?

15:57.505 --> 15:59.404
It's not gonna be easy

15:59.406 --> 16:00.472
trying to convince

16:00.474 --> 16:02.107
a world-class company

16:02.109 --> 16:04.443
to redevelop next
to a sewage plant.

16:04.445 --> 16:06.412
Well,

16:06.414 --> 16:07.679
you're creative.

16:07.681 --> 16:09.782
I'm sure you have
some great ideas.

16:09.784 --> 16:11.253
Mm-hm.

16:12.786 --> 16:14.419
I'm in.

16:14.421 --> 16:15.654
But you better take my calls

16:15.656 --> 16:17.525
when you're in the White House.

16:20.227 --> 16:23.528
It was nice chatting again
with you, Charlotte.

16:23.530 --> 16:25.034
Au revoir.

16:28.203 --> 16:29.203
Hmm.

16:58.800 --> 17:01.500
<i>And you're back
with the Lyndon and Power Show.</i>

17:01.502 --> 17:03.269
<i>So did you guys hear?
Something called</i>

17:03.271 --> 17:04.804
<i>the New London
Development Corporation</i>

17:04.806 --> 17:06.471
<i>is supposedly gonna rescue
our local economy.</i>

17:06.473 --> 17:08.574
<i>Yeah,
well, good luck with that.</i>

17:08.576 --> 17:09.909
<i>Yeah. We
wanna hear what you think.</i>

17:09.911 --> 17:13.645
Economic development
and social justice,

17:13.646 --> 17:15.448
they go hand in hand.

17:15.450 --> 17:17.249
And with this project,

17:17.251 --> 17:18.351
well, we might actually

17:18.353 --> 17:19.519
make New London hip.

17:20.588 --> 17:23.588
Imagine a Fortune 500 company

17:23.589 --> 17:24.923
in New London.

17:24.925 --> 17:26.828
- Sante.
- Cheers.

17:33.534 --> 17:37.403
Thank you again for joining me
ce soir, Howard.

17:37.405 --> 17:39.438
It's too bad your husband
couldn't join us.

17:39.440 --> 17:42.607
Well, if you
weren't such a slave driver,

17:42.609 --> 17:44.245
David might have been able to.

17:46.947 --> 17:49.414
David tells me you have
some important business

17:49.416 --> 17:50.749
to discuss.

17:50.751 --> 17:53.451
- C'est tellement vrai.
- I'm sorry?

17:53.453 --> 17:54.822
So very true.

17:59.327 --> 18:00.326
Fuck you.

18:00.328 --> 18:01.894
I found the problem.
There's a tampon

18:01.896 --> 18:03.328
- in your faucet.
- Really?

18:03.330 --> 18:04.963
<i>Yeah. Okay, well, I'm gonna go</i>

18:04.965 --> 18:07.900
to the hardware store
and pick you up a toilet kit

