35:28.642 --> 35:30.575
- Where?
- <i>It's right there.</i>

35:30.577 --> 35:32.479
It's right in the blight.

35:36.716 --> 35:41.685
Well, you have an exquisite view
of the river.

35:41.687 --> 35:43.020
Yeah.

35:43.022 --> 35:45.656
I don't really care
how exciting all of this is.

35:45.658 --> 35:46.890
I just...
nobody can force me

35:46.892 --> 35:48.526
out of my own home.

35:48.528 --> 35:50.694
Oh, no... oh.

35:50.696 --> 35:53.564
No one is forcing you, Susette.

35:53.566 --> 35:55.533
We wanna buy your home.

35:55.535 --> 35:56.801
I don't wanna sell it.

35:56.803 --> 35:58.270
I don't wanna sell it.

35:58.272 --> 36:02.774
Right, but your house
is in a parcel

36:02.776 --> 36:05.542
that has been designated

36:05.544 --> 36:07.544
for the redevelopment plan.

36:07.546 --> 36:09.881
<i>The city will help
relocate you.</i>

36:09.883 --> 36:11.549
I mean, this is a collaboration

36:11.551 --> 36:13.551
between us and the residents.

36:13.553 --> 36:16.520
Well, how are we...

36:16.522 --> 36:18.522
collaborating?

36:18.524 --> 36:19.957
Well, we'll work together

36:19.959 --> 36:21.859
and come to a mutual agreement.

36:21.861 --> 36:23.461
Oh, I'll never agree.

36:23.463 --> 36:25.497
There's no other house

36:25.499 --> 36:28.600
with this "exquisite view"
of the water

36:28.602 --> 36:31.636
that I could afford.

36:31.638 --> 36:33.638
Susette.

36:33.640 --> 36:35.973
Have you ever worked
with the poor?

36:35.975 --> 36:37.975
<i>Those people standing around</i>

36:37.977 --> 36:41.680
<i>outside of those
vacant storefronts,</i>

36:41.682 --> 36:42.680
in your neighborhood.

36:42.682 --> 36:43.982
I talk to them.

36:43.984 --> 36:46.817
You should see
their faces light up

36:46.819 --> 36:49.390
when they hear about
all of this.

36:50.756 --> 36:52.726
What about eminent domain?

36:54.428 --> 36:55.694
It's an option.

36:55.696 --> 36:56.895
But only as a last resort

36:56.897 --> 36:59.367
if people refuse to sell.

37:01.033 --> 37:06.337
If you even try to take
my property away from me,

37:06.339 --> 37:08.975
the whole world
is gonna hear about it.

37:20.821 --> 37:21.886
I want to set up a meeting

37:21.888 --> 37:23.587
with the Fort Trumbull residents

37:23.589 --> 37:26.493
and nip this in the bud
before it spreads.

37:29.463 --> 37:31.696
Hi. My name is Susette Kelo.

37:31.698 --> 37:32.830
I live in Fort Trumbull

37:32.832 --> 37:34.098
and I need to talk
to the Mayor please,

37:34.100 --> 37:35.834
- right away.
- <i>Okay.</i>

37:35.836 --> 37:38.906
<i>And can I tell him
what this is regarding?</i>

37:39.939 --> 37:41.138
It's regarding the people

37:41.140 --> 37:44.042
who are trying
to steal my house.

37:44.044 --> 37:45.810
<i>Okay. Please hold.</i>

37:45.812 --> 37:47.645
Well, I'll tell you,
I can see why they want

37:47.647 --> 37:49.814
this place.

37:49.816 --> 37:52.750
<i>Come on, Beachy.</i>

37:52.752 --> 37:53.953
<i>Is this real?</i>

37:54.854 --> 37:56.589
It might be.

37:57.957 --> 38:00.625
Is there anything
you can do to help us?

38:00.627 --> 38:01.692
<i>Well, Susette,</i>

38:01.694 --> 38:02.794
<i>the way city government works,</i>

38:02.796 --> 38:05.763
in particular New London,

38:05.765 --> 38:07.899
my options
are a little bit limited.

38:07.901 --> 38:10.033
But if you get out there,

38:10.035 --> 38:11.636
start knocking on doors,

38:11.638 --> 38:13.037
get people engaged,

38:13.039 --> 38:14.671
<i>gather up some letters
from everybody,</i>

38:14.673 --> 38:15.807
<i>I can take those letters</i>

38:15.809 --> 38:18.176
<i>down to City Council.</i>

38:18.178 --> 38:20.845
Because then I'll have
your support.

38:20.847 --> 38:23.180
And that gives me
a little bit more power.

38:23.182 --> 38:25.183
But you have to hit
the ground running.

38:25.185 --> 38:26.683
You understand?

38:26.685 --> 38:28.886
Rally the troops.

38:28.888 --> 38:30.091
We have troops?

38:32.691 --> 38:33.758
My name's Susette Kelo.

38:33.760 --> 38:34.691
I live in the pink house.

38:34.693 --> 38:37.095
<i>We're having Saturday cleanup,</i>

38:37.097 --> 38:39.430
<i>so please come if you're free.</i>

38:39.432 --> 38:40.932
And bring people.
Please. Yeah.

38:40.934 --> 38:42.600
Yeah. Invite friends.

38:42.602 --> 38:44.435
Thank you.

38:44.437 --> 38:46.837
Stop trying
to give them both.

38:46.839 --> 38:48.973
We don't have to give
each person in a couple one.

38:48.975 --> 38:50.841
It's just a waste.

38:50.843 --> 38:53.076
So I'm having this gathering
on Saturday.

38:53.078 --> 38:55.046
Invited most of the people
in the neighborhood.

38:55.048 --> 38:57.714
My house is that pink one.

39:03.789 --> 39:05.089
- Hey.
- Hi.

39:05.091 --> 39:06.991
You brought your own rake.
How great.

39:06.993 --> 39:09.060
If you don't mind signing in,

39:09.062 --> 39:10.462
and your address,

39:10.464 --> 39:11.830
even though I know
where you are.

39:11.832 --> 39:13.765
- Thank you.
- Hey, Dobbs.

39:13.767 --> 39:15.136
Thanks for coming in.

39:17.169 --> 39:20.872
I've been living here
for 40 years.

39:20.874 --> 39:22.105
To be a bus driver,

39:22.107 --> 39:23.640
and have a view
like this, huh?

39:23.642 --> 39:24.741
It's incredible.

39:24.743 --> 39:26.144
And that's why
we have to fight.

39:26.146 --> 39:28.912
I don't think this is gonna make
any difference.

39:28.914 --> 39:30.180
Look, I know these people.

39:30.182 --> 39:31.851
I don't want to join a group
of whiners.

39:33.819 --> 39:36.122
Well, will you at least
write a letter?

39:37.022 --> 39:38.925
This is all gonna blow over.

39:40.526 --> 39:42.060
Please?

39:42.062 --> 39:44.194
Oh, what the hell?

39:44.196 --> 39:45.129
Okay.

39:45.131 --> 39:47.765
I thought I was the bad one,
but really,

39:47.767 --> 39:48.765
your daughter was the bad one.

39:48.767 --> 39:51.069
- No, she instigated everything.
- No, I didn't.

39:51.071 --> 39:53.805
- Oh, stop.
- No, I didn't.

39:53.807 --> 39:57.077
My husband gave up the ghost
in this house.

39:58.245 --> 40:01.111
It's where he wanted to be.

40:01.113 --> 40:03.113
And it's where I want to be too

40:03.115 --> 40:05.616
when my time comes.

40:05.618 --> 40:07.951
My wife and I grew up
in this neighborhood.

40:07.953 --> 40:09.720
<i>Oh.</i>

40:09.722 --> 40:12.957
This is the only house
we've ever lived in.

40:12.959 --> 40:15.993
We raised our children here.

40:15.995 --> 40:19.596
This is my home.

40:19.598 --> 40:22.000
We want...

40:22.002 --> 40:24.801
to stay...

40:24.803 --> 40:25.939
here.

40:41.086 --> 40:43.754
Good evening.

40:43.756 --> 40:45.089
Charlotte!

40:45.091 --> 40:46.558
Good evening.

40:49.930 --> 40:51.895
Well, I love a man

40:51.897 --> 40:53.031
who yells my name.

40:54.767 --> 40:57.267
Woo!

40:57.269 --> 40:59.270
Folks...

40:59.272 --> 41:02.040
I know there's been
a lot of speculation

41:02.042 --> 41:04.075
about what's going on
in the neighborhood,

41:04.077 --> 41:06.944
and I thought it would be good

41:06.946 --> 41:08.779
to get together tonight

41:08.781 --> 41:10.682
and talk about it.

41:10.684 --> 41:12.118
Now first...

41:14.588 --> 41:16.287
let me tell you

41:16.289 --> 41:19.957
about a new vision
for New London.

41:19.959 --> 41:22.627
And I am here tonight

41:22.629 --> 41:26.196
to invite each
and every one of you

41:26.198 --> 41:27.899
to be a part of our team

41:27.901 --> 41:29.968
to create this vision.

41:29.970 --> 41:34.939
A New London
that is vital and hip.

41:36.843 --> 41:39.076
Hip? You mean...

41:39.078 --> 41:41.044
"High Income People" hip?

41:46.086 --> 41:48.218
All right. All right, please.

41:48.220 --> 41:50.321
Please everyone,
let's keep this civil.

41:50.323 --> 41:52.022
- What?
- <i>Oh, okay.</i>

41:52.024 --> 41:53.323
While we're keeping it civil

41:53.325 --> 41:54.926
you'll be stealing our homes.

41:54.928 --> 41:56.026
Is that right?

41:56.028 --> 41:56.894
<i>No, no, no.</i>

41:56.896 --> 41:58.363
That is not true.

41:58.365 --> 42:00.698
Everyone, no final decisions

42:00.700 --> 42:01.665
have been made.

42:01.667 --> 42:04.669
We are still looking
into every alternative.

42:04.671 --> 42:05.903
<i>Well, then why did you fire</i>

42:05.905 --> 42:07.305
the engineering firm
that suggested

42:07.307 --> 42:09.774
these homes might be spared?

42:09.776 --> 42:10.841
Well...

42:10.843 --> 42:13.276
Well, actually,
they weren't fired.

42:13.278 --> 42:15.812
Their work was done and...

42:15.814 --> 42:16.948
we both moved on.

42:16.950 --> 42:18.049
Oh, oh, excuse me.

42:18.051 --> 42:19.783
You moved on because Pfizer

42:19.785 --> 42:21.151
told you to move on.

42:21.153 --> 42:22.687
<i>You're all a bunch
of kiss-asses!</i>

42:22.689 --> 42:24.154
Let me be clear,

42:24.156 --> 42:26.957
because I know that there are

42:26.959 --> 42:29.694
some of you who view
this redevelopment

42:29.696 --> 42:30.595
as a bad thing.

42:30.597 --> 42:32.997
<i>I'm sorry, but do you see</i>

42:32.999 --> 42:36.066
kicking us out of our homes
as a bad thing?

42:36.068 --> 42:37.267
- <i>You don't think it's bad.</i>
- <i>Exactly!</i>

42:37.269 --> 42:40.171
I assure you
no one wants to kick you

42:40.173 --> 42:41.439
out of your homes.

42:42.975 --> 42:45.375
You sure got a
funny way of showing it.

42:45.377 --> 42:46.843
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

42:54.888 --> 42:59.290
Please understand
our perspective here.

42:59.292 --> 43:02.694
The most important thing
to us, to me,

43:02.696 --> 43:05.062
and I'm sure you'll all agree,

43:05.064 --> 43:07.698
is to help those in need.

43:09.068 --> 43:10.935
Yes.

43:10.937 --> 43:13.738
The jobless, the homeless,

43:13.740 --> 43:16.841
the people on the fringes
of society,

43:16.843 --> 43:19.877
they will benefit the most
from this plan.

43:19.879 --> 43:21.212
How?

43:21.214 --> 43:23.247
Pfizer's expansion to New London

43:23.249 --> 43:25.348
will increase
this city's tax revenue

43:25.350 --> 43:29.220
by $12 million a year.

43:30.890 --> 43:33.825
We are only
here to make this city

43:33.827 --> 43:35.493
that you live
in a better place.

43:35.495 --> 43:37.962
Who decides
what a better place is?

43:37.964 --> 43:39.129
You?

43:39.131 --> 43:40.865
Oh, no. No, no.

43:40.867 --> 43:41.999
Not me.

43:42.001 --> 43:43.133
Your community wants this.

43:43.135 --> 43:45.102
- No.
- Oh, yes.

43:45.104 --> 43:46.837
And your city needs this.

43:46.839 --> 43:49.073
Charlotte. Charlotte.

43:49.075 --> 43:50.341
What are you gonna do

43:50.343 --> 43:52.243
so that these people
can keep their homes?

43:52.245 --> 43:54.745
Yeah, that's right. Yeah.

43:54.747 --> 43:57.147
The best course for us
to improve our city

43:57.149 --> 43:59.116
would be to acquire
all the homes.

43:59.118 --> 44:00.917
What? This is bullshit!

44:02.021 --> 44:03.854
This is bullshit!

44:03.856 --> 44:04.888
It's bullshit.

44:04.890 --> 44:06.424
<i>It's absolute bullshit.</i>

44:06.426 --> 44:07.991
You're gonna help the homeless

44:07.993 --> 44:10.026
by kicking people
out of their homes?

44:10.028 --> 44:12.095
<i>Where do you people get off?</i>

44:12.097 --> 44:14.031
- <i>This is unbelievable.</i>
- <i>No. I think I get it.</i>

44:14.033 --> 44:15.235
I...

44:19.205 --> 44:21.339
You took one look
at our neighborhood

44:21.341 --> 44:24.341
and saw this great water view

44:24.343 --> 44:27.145
and said,
"Hey, this is pretty nice.

44:27.147 --> 44:29.113
What are all these scumbags
doing here?"

44:29.115 --> 44:30.180
Yeah. Yeah!

44:30.182 --> 44:31.915
No. No, no, no, no.

44:31.917 --> 44:35.051
"Their houses
aren't good enough.

44:35.053 --> 44:37.087
They can't be next to Pfizer.

44:37.089 --> 44:39.557
They just don't fit in."

44:39.559 --> 44:41.225
<i>That's right. That's right.</i>

44:41.227 --> 44:42.894
No. Here's the thing.

44:42.896 --> 44:44.995
Social justice

44:44.997 --> 44:47.330
and economic development,

44:47.332 --> 44:49.267
they go hand in hand.

44:53.106 --> 44:56.042
Do you think we fit in?

44:57.443 --> 44:58.975
Susette, I would like to think

44:58.977 --> 45:00.981
there's a place here
for all of us.

45:03.048 --> 45:05.985
- Thank you.
- <i>What does that mean?</i>

45:08.287 --> 45:10.020
Any other comments?

45:26.539 --> 45:28.839
<i>Pfizer tells the
NLDC what it wants,</i>

45:28.841 --> 45:31.142
<i>the NLDC goes over
to the governor's office,</i>

45:31.144 --> 45:33.477
<i>they funnel all the money
back to the NLDC</i>

45:33.479 --> 45:35.946
<i>to make all Pfizer's dreams
come true.</i>

45:35.948 --> 45:37.348
<i>They got Charlotte
talking to Pfizer,</i>

45:37.350 --> 45:38.415
<i>Pfizer's talking to Charlotte.</i>

45:38.417 --> 45:40.116
<i>At one point, she even says,</i>

45:40.118 --> 45:42.352
<i>"I don't want Pfizer
to have to look down</i>

45:42.354 --> 45:44.321
<i>on the tenements.</i>

45:44.323 --> 45:46.223
Sleazy, yeah.

45:46.225 --> 45:48.024
But not necessarily illegal.

45:48.026 --> 45:50.394
The city takes our property
by force,

45:50.396 --> 45:51.962
using our own tax money,

45:51.964 --> 45:54.131
sells it back to Pfizer
for a fucking dollar?

45:54.133 --> 45:56.100
In what fantasy world
is that legal?

45:56.102 --> 45:57.401
Who's your source?

45:57.403 --> 45:59.537
The dumpster,

45:59.539 --> 46:02.240
at the back
of the NLDC building.

46:02.242 --> 46:03.506
You're joking, right?

46:03.508 --> 46:04.975
- No, I'm not.
- You're not joking?

46:04.977 --> 46:06.310
No. Who cares
where I got it, man?

46:06.312 --> 46:08.111
You're at the paper.
Can you print it or not?

46:08.113 --> 46:09.513
- I don't know.
- What do you mean,

46:09.515 --> 46:11.249
- you don't know?
- Seriously, I don't know.

46:11.251 --> 46:13.086
- This what you do!
- Billy.

46:14.519 --> 46:16.153
Look, Billy, there's another way

46:16.155 --> 46:17.988
to handle this.

46:17.990 --> 46:19.290
We can ask the NLDC

46:19.292 --> 46:20.457
to show us the documents.

46:20.459 --> 46:22.093
Right. Yeah.
Like that's gonna happen.

46:22.095 --> 46:22.961
Exactly.

46:22.963 --> 46:24.495
At which point,
we'll file a complaint

46:24.497 --> 46:25.897
for not being compliant

46:25.899 --> 46:29.332
with the Freedom
of Information Act.

46:29.334 --> 46:32.338
Yeah, that'll be a fun headline
for the Governor.

47:07.506 --> 47:10.174
Get me Charlotte.

47:10.176 --> 47:12.475
<i>We are getting
hammered in the press.</i>

47:12.477 --> 47:13.544
<i>In addition to your plan</i>

47:13.546 --> 47:15.212
<i>to demolish the homes,</i>

47:15.214 --> 47:17.147
<i>you violate the Freedom
of Information act?</i>

47:17.149 --> 47:20.051
The NLDC is
a private corporation.

47:20.053 --> 47:20.919
Bullshit!

47:20.921 --> 47:22.386
You could have shown them
something!

47:22.388 --> 47:24.154
All right, Mr. Governor,

47:24.156 --> 47:25.323
I think this little bump

47:25.325 --> 47:27.390
in the road is far better

47:27.392 --> 47:28.558
than had I shown them

47:28.560 --> 47:30.160
even one document.

47:30.162 --> 47:31.227
<i>Mm-hm.</i>

47:31.229 --> 47:33.663
<i>Now, if you remember,</i>

47:33.665 --> 47:36.232
<i>I told you
from the very beginning</i>

47:36.234 --> 47:38.301
<i>that this was going
to be an uphill battle,</i>

47:38.303 --> 47:40.470
and...

47:40.472 --> 47:42.640
if I may toot my own horn,

47:42.642 --> 47:46.609
I have come in on time
and on budget.

47:46.611 --> 47:48.412
I am not authorizing
another dime

47:48.414 --> 47:50.281
until you clean up
this PR shitstorm.

48:12.571 --> 48:14.307
Oh, my God.

48:20.446 --> 48:21.415
Oh, my God.

48:22.314 --> 48:24.515
Excuse me.

48:24.517 --> 48:26.383
Are you the owner
of this house?

48:26.385 --> 48:28.451
I live there. Yeah.

48:28.453 --> 48:30.388
- What happened?
- There was a fire.

48:30.390 --> 48:31.589
I'm not quite sure
of the cause.

48:31.591 --> 48:33.624
Yeah. Is everything okay?

48:33.626 --> 48:35.292
- Are the people all right?
- They're fine.

48:35.294 --> 48:36.593
They're in Family Services.
They're fine.

48:36.595 --> 48:38.796
Okay. And my house?
Can I go in, or...

48:38.798 --> 48:40.064
<i>You can, but
we had to soak it down</i>

48:40.066 --> 48:41.464
<i>to protect it from the fire,</i>

48:41.466 --> 48:42.732
<i>but there could be
some water damage,</i>

48:42.734 --> 48:44.468
- or smoke damage.
- Okay. Thank you.

48:44.470 --> 48:45.535
Okay. All right.

48:56.816 --> 48:59.049
<i>Well, that's one
way to get rid of her.</i>

49:34.220 --> 49:36.453
This is unbelievable.

49:36.455 --> 49:37.624
Damn it!

49:40.526 --> 49:42.392
Okay.

49:42.394 --> 49:44.563
All right, everybody,
here's the deal.

49:46.198 --> 49:48.466
The NLDC...

49:48.468 --> 49:50.366
has gotten permits to demolish

49:50.368 --> 49:53.136
five buildings in Fort Trumbull,

49:53.138 --> 49:54.471
<i>including the house
right next door</i>

49:54.473 --> 49:55.642
<i>to this one.</i>

49:57.176 --> 49:59.410
- So, we need a lawyer.
- I think so.

49:59.412 --> 50:00.711
You need ten lawyers.

50:00.713 --> 50:02.178
What are you talking
about "a" lawyer?

50:02.180 --> 50:03.446
I deal with this
kind of stuff.

50:03.448 --> 50:04.515
I have in the past.

50:04.517 --> 50:05.549
<i>It is a pain in the ass.</i>

50:05.551 --> 50:07.283
Business that great
over at the antique store?

50:07.285 --> 50:08.785
What are you suggesting?
You, like... I mean,

50:08.787 --> 50:10.854
you could always sell
your Jag, Billy.

50:10.856 --> 50:12.823
- I mean...
- No, I'd sell the Jag.

50:12.825 --> 50:14.457
- I'd sell the Jag.
- I'd sell it, but I'm telling you we need more money...

50:14.459 --> 50:15.558
- What else you gonna chip in?
- Guys.

50:15.560 --> 50:17.394
Guys.

50:17.396 --> 50:18.696
I think I can get a guy

50:18.698 --> 50:20.466
who'll take the case for free.

50:23.301 --> 50:24.336
Is he any good?

50:28.140 --> 50:30.841
No, the hearing
isn't until February.

50:30.843 --> 50:32.776
Yeah.

50:32.778 --> 50:34.410
No, no, I've been here
15 minutes.

50:34.412 --> 50:36.215
I'm circling.
I don't know where I am.

50:40.419 --> 50:42.386
East, East, East...

50:42.388 --> 50:45.092
<i>Hey, hey, Chip, I gotta call
you right back, okay?</i>

50:51.897 --> 50:54.598
Eating, talking
on your cell phone,

50:54.600 --> 50:55.765
looking on a map.

